        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="11">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, shift transmission to neutral or park, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Gore-Tex&#174; patches will be applied in the three locations shown in Figure 1.</para>
            <figure id="f0708041" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Gore-Tex&#174; Patch Locations</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Remove headlight assembly to begin repairs (master service manual S09009 shows assembly removal from
                vehicle).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the outboard cap (Figure 2).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708042" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the inside cap (Figure 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708043" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the vent tube (Figure 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708044" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove protective backing from the patch and press tight to install the outboard patch
                    (Figure 5).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708045" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708045.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat procedure for the inboard patch (Figure 6).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708046" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708046.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat procedure for the vent tube patch (Figure 7).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708047" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install new vent cap (Figures 8 and 9).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0708048" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0708049" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0708049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install new vent tube. (new tube is in the kit) Make sure the tube opening points to
                    the back of the lamp assembly as shown in Figure 10.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f070804a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G070804A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, use Super Glue to help retain the new vent tube (Figure 11).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f070804b" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G070804B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.</caption>
            </figure>
